priorVersion.title: CDISC SDTM Result Type Response Terminology

rootItem.title: Version-agnostic anchor resource for codelist C179588

self.title: CDISC SDTM Result Type Response Terminology

definition: Terminology relevant to the values that describe the result type.
name: Result Type Response
preferredTerm: CDISC SDTM Result Type Response Terminology

terms.definition: The outward or visible aspect of an entity.
The quantity of a specified substance, which is subject to individual judgment, preference, or predetermined reference, in a unit volume or weight of another substance.
The volume consumed, produced, excreted, or otherwise changed per area per unit of time.
The quantity of a specified substance, which is based on catalytic activity, in a unit volume or weight of another substance.
The total amount of catalytic activity for a substance contained within an entity.
The catalytic activity of a component substance to the catalytic activity of the whole.
The weight of a specified component divided by the number of entities.
The volume of a specified component divided by the number of the specified component.
A diagnostic statement that is an interpretation or abstraction of an observation(s).
The quantity, expressed as the log of the moles, of a specified substance in a unit volume or weight of another substance.
The quantity, expressed as a weight, of a specified substance in a unit volume or weight of another substance.
The weight of a component substance to the weight of the whole.
The weight consumed, produced, excreted, or otherwise changed per unit of time.
The quotient of the weight of one substance divided by the weight of another substance.
A statement about the form and/or structure of a target entity.
The individual test result relative to the median value of a reference set of test results.
An absolute count of the number of entities.
The number of specified entities per unit of area.
The number of specified entities in a unit volume or weight of a substance.
The number of component entities to the total number of entities.
The number of solute particles per liter of solution.
The pressure exerted by a single component of a mixture of gases.
The difference between two numbers divided by the average of the two numbers, multiplied by 100.
An indication of the presence of an entity which, if present, is identified.
An indication of the presence of an entity which, if present, is in an amount above a predetermined threshold.
The relationship in quantity, amount, or size between two entities or activities.
The quantity of a specified substance, which is based on catalytic activity, in a unit volume or weight of another substance, relative to a comparator.
The density of a specified substance, relative to a comparator.
The quantity, expressed as a weight, of a specified substance in a unit volume or weight of another substance, relative to a comparator.
The time of a specified activity, relative to a comparator.
A number or range of numeric values that assess and order a result or response for purposes of comparison.
The quantity, expressed in moles, of a specified substance in a unit volume or weight of another substance.
The molar amount of a component substance to the molar amount of the whole.
The molar amount of substance consumed, produced, excreted, or otherwise changed per unit of time.
The quotient of the molar amount of one substance, divided by the molar amount of another substance.
The length of time during which something continues.
The quotient of one activity time interval divided by another activity time interval.
An identifiable class based on common distinguishable qualities.
The speed of an entity in a given direction.
The resistance of a liquid to sheer forces and flow. (NCI)
The amount of three dimensional space occupied by an object or the capacity of a space or container. (NCI)
The volume consumed, produced, excreted, or otherwise changed per unit of time.
